Reasoning: The paper discusses visual odometry techniques for mobile robotics and industrial automation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively covers camera-based motion estimation using computer vision techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the evolution of visual odometry techniques, which involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of visual odometry in control systems (cs.SY).
